content:
@kevinriggle i have always appreciated the house hacking a salaryman of my acquaintance did:

1) live sufficiently far from work to get a $10 daily commute allowance.
2) bike to work, tco perhaps $60 a year.
3) commute allowance, quote, “builds home equity and also a healthy body.”

@sudogene “man gifts woman alcohol” has had connotations since fermentation was discovered.

the recent change is that salaryman a buying salaryman b a bottle of alcohol may pattern match to that, even if the intent was “wait we’re both salarymen this is just how the game is played.”

@jorgeo i got patrik-san (sic) on linkedin recruiter spam yesterday and, since always look on the bright side of life, was at least happy that someone thinks i could potentially hack it as a junior rails developer.
literally every factory game causes me to spend five hours on pencil and graph paper for every one hour playing. my pride as a (recovering) salaryman is at stake.
rt @maxkriegervg: every unemployed game dev should pitch in so we can make a co-op space out of casa tallarico. it's what's owed to us
